   <!--86-->Moria Scout x 4<br>
   Plundered <!--303-->Armories x 2<br>
<br>
Pipeweed Information Management Deck by Dana &quot;Tigger&quot; Moreland<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Strategy:<br>
<br>
Bid high (6-7) and get Gandalf&#39;s cart out at the Shire Lookout Point. <br>
Play every possession you have onto the cart. Whenever you can, look at your opponent&#39;s hand. <br>
Give him the right number of twilight based on what he has. Move slowly unless you know it is safe. <br>
Manage your wounds, burdens and twilight with your pipeweed.<br>
The key to this deck is that you have the tools to clear your hand every turn, manage the &quot;beads&quot;, <br>
and look at your opponent&#39;s hand every other turn. Knowledge is power.<br>
<br>
On the shadow side, again play everything you can every turn. You will always get more. <br>
You will win eventually by overwhelming your opponent, it is just a matter of time. <br>
<br>
If you can get just 4 rare cards this deck can be improved greatly.<br>
On the Fellowship side replace the Armor and Coat of Mail with  Glamdring and Sting.<br>
These will let Gandalf and Frodo fight better but more importantly with them you can look at your<br>
opponent&#39;s hand every turn, either by exerting and using a sword or by  playing Treachery.<br>
On the shadow side replace the two Plundered Armories with a Goblin Armory and a Goblin Swarms. <br>
With these you will be able to play you weapons for free and replay more of your Minions. <br>
<br>
Please let me know what you think of this deck and what you would change to improve it. <br>
Please stick with the theme however. Remember this is a Pipeweed information management / <br>
Moria swarm deck, with no rare cards (basic form) and only 4 rare cards for the &quot;advanced&quot; version. <br>
Don&#39;t turn it into a 40 rare card Ranger/Cave Troll deck.<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
Dana &quot;Tigger&quot; Moreland (fun, fun, fun, fun, fun)<br>
